quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  84,1,"When the sky is rent asunder,"
  84,2,"And hearkens to (the Command of) its Lord, and it must needs (do so);-"
  84,3,"And when the earth is flattened out,"
  84,4,"And casts forth what is within it and becomes (clean) empty,"
  84,5,"And hearkens to (the Command of) its Lord,- and it must needs (do so);- (then will come Home the full reality)."
  84,6,"O thou man! Verily thou art ever toiling on towards thy Lord- painfully toiling,- but thou shalt meet Him."
  84,7,"Then he who is given his Record in his right hand,"
  84,8,"Soon will his account be taken by an easy reckoning,"
  84,9,"And he will turn to his people, rejoicing!"
  84,10,"But he who is given his Record behind his back,-"